    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-12-05T16:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-12-05T16:00:00-05:00" n="758"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d758">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.114 Narcotics/1394: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-12-05T16:00:00-05:00"
                            >December 5, 1935—4 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>69. Your despatch No. 77, November 6,<note n="14" xml:id="d758fn14">Not
                        printed.</note> and previous, in regard Chinese drug import permits. Please
                    inform Chinese Government that no certificate for export of narcotic drugs to
                    China will be issued except against import permit issued by Chinese Public
                    Health Administration.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
